  "name": "Building Block",
  "mood": "Prism",
  "engines": ["Obrix"],
  "description": "The most minimal expression of the Collision recipe — one brick at a time. Pulse src1 (PW=0.5, perfectly symmetric) against Saw src2 at +1 semitone, the tightest detune, producing a slow chorusing beat. proc1=LP (1650 Hz, reso=0.25) and proc2=LP (710 Hz, reso=0.38) — moderate independent filtering. proc3=Wavefolder (2900 Hz) adds gentle fold on sustained notes. fmDepth=0.1 — nearly inaudible but present, creating micro-harmonic connection. The most playable of the Prism Collision presets: straightforward action, prismatic harmonic color. Mod: Env->FilterCutoff, LFO->Pan (gentle width), Velocity->Volume, Aftertouch->proc3Cutoff. CHARACTER 0.22 — a neutral, inviting starting position.",
  "tags": ["obrix", "prism", "pulse", "saw", "constructive-collision", "wavefolder", "building", "block"],
